    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> until the water runs clear, then add it to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-red-thai-cod-curry/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your<strong> green beans </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-red-thai-cod-curry/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the onion is starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-red-thai-cod-curry/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> fish sauce </strong>and a pinch of<strong> sugar </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> coconut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-red-thai-cod-curry/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>ground paprika</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-red-thai-cod-curry/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> red Thai curry paste</strong> and<strong> halved green beans</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further or until the green beans are slightly tender</p><p>Chop your <strong>cod fillet[s] </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-red-thai-cod-curry/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the green beans are slightly tender, add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat \u2013 this is your <strong>red Thai curry</strong></p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and top the <strong>red Thai curry</strong> with your<strong> chopped cod</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for 5-6 min or until the fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>red Thai cod curry</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-red-thai-cod-curry/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> red Thai cod curry</strong> over the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice</strong></p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Garnish with your <strong>crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
